HEADWORD: Briticism
<hw>Brit"i*cism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A word, phrase,
or idiom peculiar to Great Britain; any manner of using a word or words
that is peculiar to Great Britain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

